defaultCarplus
default was established in 2000 to support the development of car clubs and ride-sharing schemes 
defaultthroughout the UK
default, in response to growing environmental concerns around private car use.
default&#xa0;
defaultOver the past decade, Carplus has played an active role in the introduction 
defaultand growth of the car club sector in the UK. From a handful of community-led car clubs there are now over 150,000 members in England alone. These members have access to over 2000 vehicles in over 50 locations across England, Wales and Scotland.
